id: pm-kexu
title: update-many --dry-run should allow filter-only preview for review and bulk-selection workflows
description: "During the 2026-07-06/07 all-status ecosystem review, 'pm update-many --filter-status open --filter-metadata-missing --dry-run --limit 200 --json' failed because no mutation flags were provided. That is defensible for mutation execution, but dry-run is also the natural safe preview for bulk-selection filters. Duplicate check: searched all statuses for update-many dry-run no mutation flags filter-only review; only closed pm-twtu covers the generic error message, while no open item tracks filter-only dry-run preview support."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 3
tags[4]: agent-ux,"area:cli",bulk-ops,review
created_at: "2026-07-06T22:29:52.125Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-14T17:05:06.440Z"
author: codex-agent
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: "update-many --dry-run can return the matched item set/count when only filters are provided, without requiring a dummy mutation flag; output is bounded and scriptable in json/toon; existing mutation-required behavior remains for non-dry-run execution; tests cover no-mutation dry-run, no-mutation real run, and at least one metadata filter."
goal: project management = context management
objective: Make bulk-selection filters safely inspectable before mutation
value: Improves audit workflows and reduces accidental bulk-mutation risk for agents.
why_now: "Audits and bulk backfill planning need safe, exact previews before mutation; forcing a fake mutation flag is error-prone for agents."
